ds`, etc.).\n\n5. **DB client conventions**: Read `/workspaces/rng-utopia/peek/src/server/db/client.ts` to understand the query function signature (does it use `pg` directly? a wrapper? pool?). Look for any helper for parsing numeric text columns or BigInt-safe lamport sums (I saw a reference to `sumLamports()` in iteration 30 history).\n\nReport back with:\n- File paths and key snippets (column names, types, indexes for rounds + closecall_rounds + game_entries.is_winner / refund detection)\n- The standard query function signature & shape\n- The existing types I should reuse (PeekGameId, PeekTableFilter, etc.)\n- Any naming conventions I should follow for a new file like `get-game-rounds.ts` / `get-flipyou-rounds.ts`\n- Anything about phase enums for FlipYou/PotShot/CloseCall (string union? lifecycle states?)\n- The format of `result_side`, `winner` fields, `is_winner` semantics\n- How \"stuck\" is currently filtered anywhere in the codebase (grep for `is_winner is null`, `phase`, `settle_attempts` in peek queries)\n\nKeep the report dense and actionable — I will use it to write the new query module."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3448,"cache_read_input_tokens":63540,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3448},"output_tokens":47,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ecdb13ab-d22c-40f2-a1b0-874b3e540ce1","uuid":"59a8b443-8e7a-4118-99fe-c284191bfd7b"}
