{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015tCCoV3LYwadTqq9o5Vvdk","type":"tool_result","content":"1\timport postgres from \"postgres\";\n2\t\n3\tlet cachedClient: ReturnType<typeof postgres> | null = null;\n4\tconst DEFAULT_CONNECT_TIMEOUT_SECONDS = 5;\n5\t\n6\texport function getDatabaseUrlFromEnv(\n7\t  env: Record<string, string | undefined> = process.env\n8\t) {\n9\t  const databaseUrl = env.DATABASE_URL;\n10\t\n11\t  if (!databaseUrl) {\n12\t    throw new Error(\"DATABASE_URL is required\");\n13\t  }\n14\t\n15\t  return databaseUrl;\n16\t}\n17\t\n18\texport function getConnectTimeoutSecondsFromEnv(\n19\t  env: Record<string, string | undefined> = process.env\n20\t) {\n21\t  const rawValue = env.PEEK_DB_CONNECT_TIMEOUT_SECONDS ?? env.PGCONNECT_TIMEOUT;\n22\t  const parsedValue = rawValue ? Number.parseInt(rawValue, 10) : Number.NaN;\n23\t\n24\t  if (Number.isFinite(parsedValue) && parsedValue > 0) {\n25\t    return parsedValue;\n26\t  }\n27\t\n28\t  return DEFAULT_CONNECT_TIMEOUT_SECONDS;\n29\t}\n30\t\n31\texport function getSqlClient() {\n32\t  if (!cachedClient) {\n33\t    cachedClient = postgres(getDatabaseUrlFromEnv(), {\n34\t      max: 5,\n35\t      prepare: true,\n36\t      connect_timeout: getConnectTimeoutSecondsFromEnv(),\n37\t    });\n38\t  }\n39\t\n40\t  return cachedClient;\n41\t}\n42\t\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_0189zm3YvBvduAPooCasBMvk","session_id":"ecdb13ab-d22c-40f2-a1b0-874b3e540ce1","uuid":"1e2bf305-6e47-4998-8720-237e2879c5f5","timestamp":"2026-04-25T12:57:47.528Z"}
