{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0189zm3YvBvduAPooCasBMvk","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent. Now I have comprehensive understanding. Let me create a detailed report:\n\n## COMPREHENSIVE PEEK QUERY IMPLEMENTATION GUIDE\n\n### 1. DATABASE SCHEMA: Rounds & Related Tables\n\n#### **rounds table** (migration 001)\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE rounds (\n  pda              TEXT         PRIMARY KEY,\n  game             TEXT         NOT NULL CHECK (game IN ('flipyou', 'potshot')),\n  creator          TEXT         NOT NULL,\n  server_key       TEXT         NOT NULL,\n  secret           BYTEA        NOT NULL,\n  commitment       BYTEA        NOT NULL,\n  amount_lamports  BIGINT       NOT NULL,\n  side             SMALLINT     NOT NULL,\n  match_id         TEXT         NOT NULL,\n  phase            TEXT         NOT NULL CHECK (phase IN ('created', 'locked', 'settling', 'settled', 'expired')),\n  target_slot      BIGINT,\n  settle_tx        TEXT,\n  settle_attempts  INT          DEFAULT 0,\n  result_hash      BYTEA,\n  result_side      SMALLINT,\n  winner           TEXT,\n  created_at       TIMESTAMPTZ  NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),\n  updated_at       TIMESTAMPTZ  NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),\n  settled_at       TIMESTAMPTZ\n);\n-- Indexes: phase, creator, match_id, settled (DESC) WHERE phase='settled'\n```\n\n#### **closecall_rounds table** (migration 004)\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE closecall_rounds (\n  round_id        TEXT         PRIMARY KEY,\n  pda             TEXT         UNIQUE NOT NULL,\n  server_key      TEXT         NOT NULL,\n  phase           TEXT         NOT NULL DEFAULT 'open' CHECK (phase IN ('open', 'settled', 'refunded')),\n  open_price      BIGINT       NOT NULL,\n  open_price_expo INT          NOT NULL,\n  close_price     BIGINT,\n  outcome         TEXT         NOT NULL DEFAULT 'pending' CHECK (outcome IN ('pending', 'green', 'red', 'refund')),\n  green_pool      BIGINT       NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n  red_pool        BIGINT       NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n  total_fee       BIGINT       NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n  settle_tx       TEXT,\n  created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ  NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),\n  settled_at      TIMESTAMPTZ\n);\n-- Indexes: phase, settled_at (DESC), settled (DESC) WHERE phase='settled'\n```\n\n#### **game_entries table** (migration 007) — Single source of truth\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE game_entries (\n  id              BIGINT GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY,\n  user_id         TEXT         NOT NULL,\n  wallet          TEXT         NOT NULL,\n  game            TEXT         NOT NULL CHECK (game IN ('flipyou', 'potshot', 'closecall')),\n  round_pda       TEXT         NOT NULL,\n  match_id        TEXT         NOT NULL,\n  amount_lamports BIGINT       NOT NULL,\n  side            TEXT,           -- nullable for closecall\n  is_winner       BOOLEAN,         -- NULL = refunded (payout_lamports = amount_lamports)\n  payout_lamports BIGINT       NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n  created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ  NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),\n  settled_at      TIMESTAMPTZ,\n  UNIQUE (wallet, round_pda)\n);\n-- Indexes: settled (DESC), game+settled, user+settled, round_pda\n```\n\n#### **transactions table** (migration 008)\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE transactions (\n  id              BIGINT GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY,\n  user_id         TEXT,\n  wallet          TEXT         NOT NULL,\n  game            TEXT         NOT NULL CHECK (game IN ('flipyou', 'potshot', 'closecall')),\n  match_id        TEXT         NOT NULL,\n  tx_type         TEXT         NOT NULL CHECK (tx_type IN ('deposit', 'payout', 'refund')),\n  amount_lamports BIGINT       NOT NULL,\n  tx_sig          TEXT         NOT NULL,\n  created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ  NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n);\n```\n\n**No ALTER TABLE statements found** — schema is stable.\n\n---\n\n### 2. STANDARD QUERY FUNCTION SIGNATURE & SHAPE\n\nAll query functions in peek follow this pattern:\n\n```typescript\nexport type QueryOptions = {\n  sql?: Sql;  // postgres client; defaults to getSqlClient() if omitted\n  now?: Date; // for metric asOf timestamps; defaults to new Date()\n  // Feature-specific options (limits, filters) added here\n};\n\nexport async function getMyQuery(\n  options: QueryOptions = {},\n): Promise<MyReturnType> {\n  const sql = options.sql ?? (getSqlClient() as unknown as Sql);\n  const now = options.now ?? new Date();\n  \n  // Single query or Promise.all([...]) for parallel queries\n  // Return typed view model\n}\n```\n\n**Key patterns:**\n- DB client is injected via `options.sql` for testability; defaults to `getSqlClient()` (postgres package, typed raw SQL)\n- All queries use postgres template literals with interpolated values (safe via prepared statements)\n- Lamport sums (BigInt-sensitive) use `sumLamports()` helper to preserve u64 precision\n- String count/numeric columns from `::int` or `::text` casts coerce via `readInt()` / `readSum()` helpers\n- Metrics carry full FR-4 bookkeeping: `{ id, label, value, valueDisplay, unit, source, windowLabel, asOf, definition, freshness, drilldownHref }`\n\n---\n\n### 3. EXISTING TYPES & REUSABLE PRIMITIVES\n\nFrom `/workspaces/rng-utopia/peek/src/lib/types/peek.ts`:\n\n#### **Game ID & Phases**\n```typescript\nexport type PeekGameId = \"flipyou\" | \"potshot\" | \"closecall\";\nexport const PEEK_GAME_IDS: ReadonlyArray<PeekGameId> = [\"flipyou\", \"potshot\", \"closecall\"];\n\n// FlipYou/PotShot phases: 'created' | 'locked' | 'settling' | 'settled' | 'expired' (TEXT CHECK constraint)\n// CloseCall phases: 'open' | 'settled' | 'refunded'\n```\n\n#### **Core Peek Types**\n```typescript\nexport type PeekPagination = {\n  page: number;\n  pageSize: number;\n  totalCount: number;\n  totalPages: number;\n};\n\nexport type PeekSortDirection = \"asc\" | \"desc\";\nexport type PeekTableSort = {\n  column: string;\n  direction: PeekSortDirection;\n};\n\nexport type PeekTableFilter = {\n  id: string;\n  label: string;\n  kind: PeekFilterKind; // \"text\" | \"select\" | \"boolean\" | \"date\" | \"dateRange\"\n  value: string | null;\n  options: ReadonlyArray<PeekFilterOption> | null;\n  placeholder: string | null;\n  required: boolean;\n};\n\nexport type PeekTableRowBase = {\n  id: string;\n  href: string | null;\n};\n\nexport type PeekTableViewModel<TRow extends PeekTableRowBase> = {\n  columns: ReadonlyArray<PeekTableColumn>;\n  rows: ReadonlyArray<TRow>;\n  pagination: PeekPagination;\n  filters: ReadonlyArray<PeekTableFilter>;\n  sort: PeekTableSort | null;\n  empty: PeekEmptyState;\n};\n\nexport type PeekMetric = {\n  id: string;\n  label: string;\n  value: number | string | null;\n  valueDisplay: string;\n  unit: string | null;\n  source: string;\n  windowLabel: string;\n  asOf: string | null;\n  definition: string;\n  freshness: \"live\" | \"cached\" | \"manual\" | \"sampled\";\n  drilldownHref: string | null;\n};\n```\n\n#### **Game-Entry Row Type** (already defined, reusable)\n```typescript\nexport type PeekGameEntryRow = {\n  id: string;\n  game: string;\n  roundPda: string;\n  matchId: string;\n  amountLamports: string;    // text for u64 precision\n  side: string | null;\n  isWinner: boolean | null;  // null = refunded\n  payoutLamports: string;    // text for u64 precision\n  createdAt: string;\n  settledAt: string | null;\n};\n```\n\n#### **Existing Metric ID Enums**\n```typescript\nexport type PeekCommandCenterAttentionId =\n  | \"failed_claims\"\n  | \"dead_queue_events\"\n  | \"stuck_rounds_flipyou_potshot\"\n  | \"stuck_rounds_closecall\"\n  | /* ... */;\n\nexport type PeekExportEntity = \"users\" | \"referrers\" | /* ... */ | \"rounds\" | \"transactions\" | /* ... */;\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. STUCK-STATE FILTER LOGIC\n\nFrom `get-command-center-attention.ts` (lines 130–144):\n\n#### **Stuck FlipYou/PotShot Rounds:**\n```typescript\n// Thresholds:\nstuckRoundsAgeMinutes: 5,              // default\nstuckRoundsMaxSettleAttempts: 3,       // default\n\n// Query:\nSELECT COUNT(*) FROM rounds\nWHERE phase IN ('created', 'locked', 'settling')\n  AND (\n    created_at < now() - INTERVAL '5 minutes'\n    OR settle_attempts > 3\n  );\n```\n\n**Stuck semantics:**\n- NOT in terminal state (phase ∉ {'settled', 'expired'})\n- AND (older than age threshold OR settle_attempts > max)\n\n#### **Stuck CloseCall Rounds:**\n```typescript\n// Threshold:\nstuckCloseCallAgeMinutes: 5\n\n// Query:\nSELECT COUNT(*) FROM closecall_rounds\nWHERE phase = 'open'\n  AND created_at < now() - INTERVAL '5 minutes';\n```\n\n**Stuck semantics:**\n- Still in 'open' phase\n- AND older than age threshold (rounds settle on minute boundaries via Pyth)\n\n---\n\n### 5. REFUND DETECTION & is_winner SEMANTICS\n\nFrom migration 007 comment and `get-games-overview.ts`:\n\n```\nRefunded entries: is_winner = NULL, payout_lamports = amount_lamports.\n```\n\n**Filters in existing queries:**\n- **Settled:** `settled_at IS NOT NULL`\n- **Refunded:** `settled_at IS NOT NULL AND is_winner IS NULL`\n- **Wins:** `is_winner = TRUE`\n- **Losses:** `is_winner = FALSE`\n\nExample from `get-games-overview.ts` (line 161):\n```typescript\ncount(*) filter (where settled_at is not null and is_winner is null)::int as \"refund_entries\",\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. STANDARD QUERY FUNCTION SHAPE & NAMING CONVENTIONS\n\nBased on existing patterns (`get-games-overview.ts`, `get-peek-user-detail.ts`, `get-growth-referrals.ts`):\n\n#### **File naming:**\n- `get-games-overview.ts` — aggregated metrics + overview rows\n- `get-peek-user-detail.ts` — deep drill-down on one user\n- `get-growth-referrals.ts` — multi-function module (overview + list + graph)\n- **Recommendation for game rounds:** `get-game-rounds.ts` or `get-rounds-detail.ts` if grouping flipyou/potshot/closecall\n\n#### **Export structure:**\n```typescript\n// Constants\nexport const PEEK_GAME_ROUNDS_DEFAULT_LIMIT = 50;\nexport const PEEK_GAME_ROUNDS_MAX_LIMIT = 250;\n\n// Options type\nexport type GetGameRoundsOptions = {\n  sql?: Sql;\n  game: PeekGameId;\n  limit?: number;\n  filters?: Partial<GameRoundsFilters>;\n  sort?: PeekTableSort | null;\n  page?: number;\n};\n\n// Helper types for internal row mapping\ntype DBRoundRow = {\n  pda: string;\n  game: PeekGameId;\n  matchId: string;\n  phase: string;\n  creator: string | null;\n  /* ... game-specific fields ... */\n};\n\n// Exported row type extending PeekTableRowBase\nexport type PeekGameRoundRow = PeekTableRowBase & {\n  game: PeekGameId;\n  roundPda: string;\n  matchId: string;\n  phase: string;\n  creator: string | null;\n  /* ... */\n};\n\n// Main query function\nexport async function getGameRounds(\n  options: GetGameRoundsOptions = {},\n): Promise<PeekTableViewModel<PeekGameRoundRow>> {\n  const sql = options.sql ?? getSqlClient();\n  // ...\n  return {\n    columns: [/* ... */],\n    rows: [/* ... */],\n    pagination: { page, pageSize, totalCount, totalPages },\n    filters: [/* ... */],\n    sort: sort ?? null,\n    empty: { title: \"...\", body: null },\n  };\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 7. LAMPORT PRECISION & BIGINT HANDLING\n\nFrom `get-games-overview.ts`:\n\n```typescript\nfunction sumLamports(values: ReadonlyArray<string>): string {\n  // BigInt sum keeps u64 precision across per-game lamport totals; values\n  // are strings from the postgres driver.\n  let total = 0n;\n  for (const v of values) {\n    if (!v) continue;\n    try {\n      total += BigInt(v);\n    } catch {\n      // ignore unparsable values\n    }\n  }\n  return total.toString();\n}\n\nfunction readInt(value: number | string | null | undefined): number {\n  if (typeof value === \"number\" && Number.isFinite(value)) return value;\n  if (typeof value === \"string\") {\n    const parsed = Number.parseInt(value, 10);\n    return Number.isFinite(parsed) ? parsed : 0;\n  }\n  return 0;\n}\n\nfunction readSum(value: string | null | undefined): string {\n  return typeof value === \"string\" && value.length > 0 ? value : \"0\";\n}\n```\n\n**Rule:** All lamport sums and u64-sensitive counts arrive as `text` from postgres (due to `::text` cast or string BIGINT coercion); coerce via these helpers before display.\n\n---\n\n### 8. TEST SCAFFOLDING & MOCKING PATTERN\n\nFrom `get-games-overview.test.ts`:\n\n```typescript\ntype SqlCall = {\n  text: string;\n  values: ReadonlyArray<unknown>;\n};\n\ntype ResponseValue = ReadonlyArray<Record<string, unknown>> | Error;\n\ntype SqlMock = {\n  sql: Sql;\n  calls: ReadonlyArray<SqlCall>;\n};\n\nfunction createSqlMock(responses: ReadonlyArray<ResponseValue>): SqlMock {\n  const calls: SqlCall[] = [];\n  let cursor = 0;\n\n  const fn = (strings: TemplateStringsArray, ...values: unknown[]) => {\n    const text = [...strings].join(\"?\");\n    calls.push({ text, values: [...values] });\n    const next = responses[cursor++];\n    if (next instanceof Error) return Promise.reject(next);\n    return Promise.resolve(next ?? []);\n  };\n\n  const sql = fn as unknown as Sql;\n  return { sql, calls };\n}\n\n// Usage:\nconst mock = createSqlMock([\n  [/* first query response */],\n  [/* second query response */],\n]);\n\nconst result = await getGamesOverview({ sql: mock.sql, now });\n\nexpect(mock.calls).toHaveLength(2);\nexpect(mock.calls[0].text).toContain(\"from game_entries\");\n```\n\n**Key assertions:**\n- Count of parallel queries via `Promise.all()`\n- SQL text fragments (no exact match, use `.toContain()` for robustness)\n- Error handling: `expect(...).rejects.toThrow()`\n- String/number coercion tests (postgres returns text for `::int` casts)\n- Pagination + filtering behavior\n- Empty-state handling (zero-fill missing rows)\n\n---\n\n### 9. COMMAND-CENTER \"STUCK\" INTEGRATION\n\nThe peek types already define drill-down hrefs for stuck metrics:\n\n```typescript\n// From types:\nexport type PeekCommandCenterAttentionId =\n  | \"stuck_rounds_flipyou_potshot\"\n  | \"stuck_rounds_closecall\";\n\n// From get-command-center-attention.ts:\ndrilldownHref: \"/games?stuck=true\",           // flipyou/potshot stuck drill\ndrilldownHref: \"/games/closecall?stuck=true\", // closecall stuck drill\n```\n\n**If implementing per-game drill-down pages**, expect URL params like:\n- `?game=flipyou&stuck=true`\n- `?game=closecall&stuck=true`\n\n---\n\n### 10. PHASE ENUM & SETTLEMENT LIFECYCLE\n\n#### **FlipYou/PotShot (rounds table):**\n- `'created'` — round created, awaiting join\n- `'locked'` — join closed, awaiting commit reveal\n- `'settling'` — settlement in progress\n- `'settled'` — terminal, result finalized\n- `'expired'` — terminal, no settlement attempted\n\n#### **CloseCall (closecall_rounds table):**\n- `'open'` — round accepting bets\n- `'settled'` — terminal, Pyth resolved, payouts distributed\n- `'refunded'` — terminal, all bets refunded (e.g., circuit breaker)\n\n**Stuck detection:**\n- FlipYou/PotShot: NOT in {'settled', 'expired'}\n- CloseCall: = 'open'\n\n---\n\n### 11. KEY COLUMN NAMES & FIELD MAPPING\n\n#### **Rounds → Peek Row Mapping:**\n```\nDB Column           Peek Field (camelCase)\n---                 ---\npda                 roundPda / id (primary href)\ngame                game (PeekGameId)\nmatch_id            matchId\nphase               phase\ncreator             creator\ncreated_at::text    createdAt\nupdated_at::text    updatedAt\nsettled_at::text    settledAt\nsettle_attempts     settleAttempts\nsettle_tx           settleTx\nresult_side         resultSide\nwinner              winner\namount_lamports     amountLamports (if joining game_entries)\n```\n\n#### **CloseCall Rounds → Peek Row Mapping:**\n```\nDB Column           Peek Field\n---                 ---\npda                 roundPda / id\nround_id            matchId\nphase               phase\noutcome             outcome (pending|green|red|refund)\ncreated_at::text    createdAt\nsettled_at::text    settledAt\nopen_price          openPrice\nclose_price         closePrice\ngreen_pool          greenPool (lamports, text)\nred_pool            redPool (lamports, text)\ntotal_fee           totalFee (lamports, text)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 12. PAGINATION & LIMITS CONVENTIONS\n\nFrom `get-growth-referrals.ts`:\n\n```typescript\n// Per-feature constants:\nexport const PEEK_GROWTH_CLAIMS_DEFAULT_LIMIT = 100;\nexport const PEEK_GROWTH_CLAIMS_MAX_LIMIT = 500;\n\n// Helper:\nfunction clampLimit(\n  raw: number | undefined,\n  fallback: number,\n  max: number,\n): number {\n  if (typeof raw !== \"number\" || !Number.isFinite(raw)) return fallback;\n  const floored = Math.floor(raw);\n  if (floored <= 0) return 1;\n  return Math.min(max, floored);\n}\n\n// In function:\nconst limit = clampLimit(options.limit, DEFAULT_LIMIT, MAX_LIMIT);\n```\n\n**Pagination formula:**\n```typescript\nconst totalPages = Math.max(1, Math.ceil(totalCount / pageSize));\nconst offset = (page - 1) * pageSize;\n// In SQL: LIMIT pageSize OFFSET offset\n```\n\n---\n\n### 13. FILTER TYPE PATTERNS\n\nFrom `peek.ts`:\n\n```typescript\nexport type PeekTableFilter = {\n  id: string;                    // URL-addressable filter key\n  label: string;                 // Human-readable name\n  kind: PeekFilterKind;          // \"text\" | \"select\" | \"boolean\" | \"date\" | \"dateRange\"\n  value: string | null;          // Current filter value (URL param)\n  options: ReadonlyArray<PeekFilterOption> | null;  // For \"select\" kind\n  placeholder: string | null;\n  required: boolean;\n};\n\nexport type PeekFilterOption = {\n  value: string;\n  label: string;\n};\n\n// Example filters for game rounds:\nconst filters: PeekTableFilter[] = [\n  {\n    id: \"game\",\n    label: \"Game\",\n    kind: \"select\",\n    value: options.filters?.game ?? null,\n    options: PEEK_GAME_IDS.map(g => ({ value: g, label: g })),\n    placeholder: null,\n    required: false,\n  },\n  {\n    id: \"phase\",\n    label: \"Phase\",\n    kind: \"select\",\n    value: options.filters?.phase ?? null,\n    options: [\"created\", \"locked\", \"settling\", \"settled\", \"expired\"].map(p => \n      ({ value: p, label: p })\n    ),\n    placeholder: null,\n    required: false,\n  },\n  {\n    id: \"stuck\",\n    label: \"Stuck status\",\n    kind: \"boolean\",\n    value: options.filters?.stuck ?? null,\n    options: null,\n    placeholder: null,\n    required: false,\n  },\n];\n```\n\n---\n\n### SUMMARY: Quick Reference for `get-game-rounds.ts`\n\n1. **Client:** `const sql = options.sql ?? getSqlClient() as unknown as Sql`\n2. **Refunds:** `is_winner IS NULL AND settled_at IS NOT NULL`\n3. **Stuck (flipyou/potshot):** `phase IN ('created','locked','settling') AND (created_at < now()-interval OR settle_attempts > threshold)`\n4. **Stuck (closecall):** `phase = 'open' AND created_at < now()-interval`\n5. **BigInt sums:** Use `sumLamports()` helper + `readInt()` / `readSum()` for type coercion\n6. **Pagination:** `OFFSET (page-1)*pageSize LIMIT pageSize`, compute totalPages\n7. **Return type:** `PeekTableViewModel<YourRowType extends PeekTableRowBase>`\n8. **Tests:** Mock SQL with `createSqlMock([responses])`, assert on query counts + text fragments\n9. **Game ID:** Type as `PeekGameId` (literal union of three), filter via `PEEK_GAME_IDS` array check\n10. **Metrics:** Full FR-4 bookkeeping if returning summary strip alongside detail rows\n\nAll files are read-only; no ALTERs in migrations. Phase/game enums enforced by CHECK constraints at the DB level."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ecdb13ab-d22c-40f2-a1b0-874b3e540ce1","uuid":"9a8bc374-9481-4caf-afef-0ed8595c725e","timestamp":"2026-04-25T12:59:00.090Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I'm implementing per-game round queries for the peek admin app. I need a thorough understanding of:\n\n1. **Existing query patterns in peek**: Read all files in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/peek/src/server/db/queries/` to understand the established patterns for query function shape, error handling, returning view models, parameter shape, pagination/limits, and how they connect to `peek/src/lib/types/peek.ts`.\n\n2. **Existing types in peek**: Read `/workspaces/rng-utopia/peek/src/lib/types/peek.ts` and `/workspaces/rng-utopia/peek/src/lib/access-policy.ts` to understand the established type primitives (TableFilter, Pagination, MetricMetadata, table-row shapes, etc.). Look for any existing `PEEK_GAME_IDS`, `PeekGameId`, or game-related types that I should reuse.\n\n3. **Existing test patterns**: Read 1-2 representative files in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/peek/src/server/db/queries/__tests__/` (e.g., `get-games-overview.test.ts`, `get-peek-user-detail.test.ts`) to understand test scaffolding, mocking the DB client, and assertion conventions.\n\n4. **Schema for rounds tables**:\n   - Read `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/migrations/001_init.sql` (rounds table — used for FlipYou + Pot Shot)\n   - Read `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/migrations/004_closecall_rounds.sql` (closecall_rounds table)\n   - Read `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/migrations/007_game_entries.sql` (game_entries — needed for \"settled entries without expected tx\" stuck-state filter)\n   - Read `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/migrations/008_transactions.sql` (transactions table)\n   - Look for any later migrations that ALTER these tables (grep for `ALTER TABLE rounds`, `ALTER TABLE closecall_rounds`, etc.).\n\n5. **DB client conventions**: Read `/workspaces/rng-utopia/peek/src/server/db/client.ts` to understand the query function signature (does it use `pg` directly? a wrapper? pool?). Look for any helper for parsing numeric text columns or BigInt-safe lamport sums (I saw a reference to `sumLamports()` in iteration 30 history).\n\nReport back with:\n- File paths and key snippets (column names, types, indexes for rounds + closecall_rounds + game_entries.is_winner / refund detection)\n- The standard query function signature & shape\n- The existing types I should reuse (PeekGameId, PeekTableFilter, etc.)\n- Any naming conventions I should follow for a new file like `get-game-rounds.ts` / `get-flipyou-rounds.ts`\n- Anything about phase enums for FlipYou/PotShot/CloseCall (string union? lifecycle states?)\n- The format of `result_side`, `winner` fields, `is_winner` semantics\n- How \"stuck\" is currently filtered anywhere in the codebase (grep for `is_winner is null`, `phase`, `settle_attempts` in peek queries)\n\nKeep the report dense and actionable — I will use it to write the new query module.","agentId":"a3da859113ac058c2","agentType":"Explore","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent. Now I have comprehensive understanding. Let me create a detailed report:\n\n## COMPREHENSIVE PEEK QUERY IMPLEMENTATION GUIDE\n\n### 1. DATABASE SCHEMA: Rounds & Related Tables\n\n#### **rounds table** (migration 001)\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE rounds (\n  pda              TEXT         PRIMARY KEY,\n  game             TEXT         NOT NULL CHECK (game IN ('flipyou', 'potshot')),\n  creator          TEXT         NOT NULL,\n  server_key       TEXT         NOT NULL,\n  secret           BYTEA        NOT NULL,\n  commitment       BYTEA        NOT NULL,\n  amount_lamports  BIGINT       NOT NULL,\n  side             SMALLINT     NOT NULL,\n  match_id         TEXT         NOT NULL,\n  phase            TEXT         NOT NULL CHECK (phase IN ('created', 'locked', 'settling', 'settled', 'expired')),\n  target_slot      BIGINT,\n  settle_tx        TEXT,\n  settle_attempts  INT          DEFAULT 0,\n  result_hash      BYTEA,\n  result_side      SMALLINT,\n  winner           TEXT,\n  created_at       TIMESTAMPTZ  NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),\n  updated_at       TIMESTAMPTZ  NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),\n  settled_at       TIMESTAMPTZ\n);\n-- Indexes: phase, creator, match_id, settled (DESC) WHERE phase='settled'\n```\n\n#### **closecall_rounds table** (migration 004)\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE closecall_rounds (\n  round_id        TEXT         PRIMARY KEY,\n  pda             TEXT         UNIQUE NOT NULL,\n  server_key      TEXT         NOT NULL,\n  phase           TEXT         NOT NULL DEFAULT 'open' CHECK (phase IN ('open', 'settled', 'refunded')),\n  open_price      BIGINT       NOT NULL,\n  open_price_expo INT          NOT NULL,\n  close_price     BIGINT,\n  outcome         TEXT         NOT NULL DEFAULT 'pending' CHECK (outcome IN ('pending', 'green', 'red', 'refund')),\n  green_pool      BIGINT       NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n  red_pool        BIGINT       NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n  total_fee       BIGINT       NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n  settle_tx       TEXT,\n  created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ  NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),\n  settled_at      TIMESTAMPTZ\n);\n-- Indexes: phase, settled_at (DESC), settled (DESC) WHERE phase='settled'\n```\n\n#### **game_entries table** (migration 007) — Single source of truth\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE game_entries (\n  id              BIGINT GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY,\n  user_id         TEXT         NOT NULL,\n  wallet          TEXT         NOT NULL,\n  game            TEXT         NOT NULL CHECK (game IN ('flipyou', 'potshot', 'closecall')),\n  round_pda       TEXT         NOT NULL,\n  match_id        TEXT         NOT NULL,\n  amount_lamports BIGINT       NOT NULL,\n  side            TEXT,           -- nullable for closecall\n  is_winner       BOOLEAN,         -- NULL = refunded (payout_lamports = amount_lamports)\n  payout_lamports BIGINT       NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n  created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ  NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),\n  settled_at      TIMESTAMPTZ,\n  UNIQUE (wallet, round_pda)\n);\n-- Indexes: settled (DESC), game+settled, user+settled, round_pda\n```\n\n#### **transactions table** (migration 008)\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE transactions (\n  id              BIGINT GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY,\n  user_id         TEXT,\n  wallet          TEXT         NOT NULL,\n  game            TEXT         NOT NULL CHECK (game IN ('flipyou', 'potshot', 'closecall')),\n  match_id        TEXT         NOT NULL,\n  tx_type         TEXT         NOT NULL CHECK (tx_type IN ('deposit', 'payout', 'refund')),\n  amount_lamports BIGINT       NOT NULL,\n  tx_sig          TEXT         NOT NULL,\n  created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ  NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n);\n```\n\n**No ALTER TABLE statements found** — schema is stable.\n\n---\n\n### 2. STANDARD QUERY FUNCTION SIGNATURE & SHAPE\n\nAll query functions in peek follow this pattern:\n\n```typescript\nexport type QueryOptions = {\n  sql?: Sql;  // postgres client; defaults to getSqlClient() if omitted\n  now?: Date; // for metric asOf timestamps; defaults to new Date()\n  // Feature-specific options (limits, filters) added here\n};\n\nexport async function getMyQuery(\n  options: QueryOptions = {},\n): Promise<MyReturnType> {\n  const sql = options.sql ?? (getSqlClient() as unknown as Sql);\n  const now = options.now ?? new Date();\n  \n  // Single query or Promise.all([...]) for parallel queries\n  // Return typed view model\n}\n```\n\n**Key patterns:**\n- DB client is injected via `options.sql` for testability; defaults to `getSqlClient()` (postgres package, typed raw SQL)\n- All queries use postgres template literals with interpolated values (safe via prepared statements)\n- Lamport sums (BigInt-sensitive) use `sumLamports()` helper to preserve u64 precision\n- String count/numeric columns from `::int` or `::text` casts coerce via `readInt()` / `readSum()` helpers\n- Metrics carry full FR-4 bookkeeping: `{ id, label, value, valueDisplay, unit, source, windowLabel, asOf, definition, freshness, drilldownHref }`\n\n---\n\n### 3. EXISTING TYPES & REUSABLE PRIMITIVES\n\nFrom `/workspaces/rng-utopia/peek/src/lib/types/peek.ts`:\n\n#### **Game ID & Phases**\n```typescript\nexport type PeekGameId = \"flipyou\" | \"potshot\" | \"closecall\";\nexport const PEEK_GAME_IDS: ReadonlyArray<PeekGameId> = [\"flipyou\", \"potshot\", \"closecall\"];\n\n// FlipYou/PotShot phases: 'created' | 'locked' | 'settling' | 'settled' | 'expired' (TEXT CHECK constraint)\n// CloseCall phases: 'open' | 'settled' | 'refunded'\n```\n\n#### **Core Peek Types**\n```typescript\nexport type PeekPagination = {\n  page: number;\n  pageSize: number;\n  totalCount: number;\n  totalPages: number;\n};\n\nexport type PeekSortDirection = \"asc\" | \"desc\";\nexport type PeekTableSort = {\n  column: string;\n  direction: PeekSortDirection;\n};\n\nexport type PeekTableFilter = {\n  id: string;\n  label: string;\n  kind: PeekFilterKind; // \"text\" | \"select\" | \"boolean\" | \"date\" | \"dateRange\"\n  value: string | null;\n  options: ReadonlyArray<PeekFilterOption> | null;\n  placeholder: string | null;\n  required: boolean;\n};\n\nexport type PeekTableRowBase = {\n  id: string;\n  href: string | null;\n};\n\nexport type PeekTableViewModel<TRow extends PeekTableRowBase> = {\n  columns: ReadonlyArray<PeekTableColumn>;\n  rows: ReadonlyArray<TRow>;\n  pagination: PeekPagination;\n  filters: ReadonlyArray<PeekTableFilter>;\n  sort: PeekTableSort | null;\n  empty: PeekEmptyState;\n};\n\nexport type PeekMetric = {\n  id: string;\n  label: string;\n  value: number | string | null;\n  valueDisplay: string;\n  unit: string | null;\n  source: string;\n  windowLabel: string;\n  asOf: string | null;\n  definition: string;\n  freshness: \"live\" | \"cached\" | \"manual\" | \"sampled\";\n  drilldownHref: string | null;\n};\n```\n\n#### **Game-Entry Row Type** (already defined, reusable)\n```typescript\nexport type PeekGameEntryRow = {\n  id: string;\n  game: string;\n  roundPda: string;\n  matchId: string;\n  amountLamports: string;    // text for u64 precision\n  side: string | null;\n  isWinner: boolean | null;  // null = refunded\n  payoutLamports: string;    // text for u64 precision\n  createdAt: string;\n  settledAt: string | null;\n};\n```\n\n#### **Existing Metric ID Enums**\n```typescript\nexport type PeekCommandCenterAttentionId =\n  | \"failed_claims\"\n  | \"dead_queue_events\"\n  | \"stuck_rounds_flipyou_potshot\"\n  | \"stuck_rounds_closecall\"\n  | /* ... */;\n\nexport type PeekExportEntity = \"users\" | \"referrers\" | /* ... */ | \"rounds\" | \"transactions\" | /* ... */;\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. STUCK-STATE FILTER LOGIC\n\nFrom `get-command-center-attention.ts` (lines 130–144):\n\n#### **Stuck FlipYou/PotShot Rounds:**\n```typescript\n// Thresholds:\nstuckRoundsAgeMinutes: 5,              // default\nstuckRoundsMaxSettleAttempts: 3,       // default\n\n// Query:\nSELECT COUNT(*) FROM rounds\nWHERE phase IN ('created', 'locked', 'settling')\n  AND (\n    created_at < now() - INTERVAL '5 minutes'\n    OR settle_attempts > 3\n  );\n```\n\n**Stuck semantics:**\n- NOT in terminal state (phase ∉ {'settled', 'expired'})\n- AND (older than age threshold OR settle_attempts > max)\n\n#### **Stuck CloseCall Rounds:**\n```typescript\n// Threshold:\nstuckCloseCallAgeMinutes: 5\n\n// Query:\nSELECT COUNT(*) FROM closecall_rounds\nWHERE phase = 'open'\n  AND created_at < now() - INTERVAL '5 minutes';\n```\n\n**Stuck semantics:**\n- Still in 'open' phase\n- AND older than age threshold (rounds settle on minute boundaries via Pyth)\n\n---\n\n### 5. REFUND DETECTION & is_winner SEMANTICS\n\nFrom migration 007 comment and `get-games-overview.ts`:\n\n```\nRefunded entries: is_winner = NULL, payout_lamports = amount_lamports.\n```\n\n**Filters in existing queries:**\n- **Settled:** `settled_at IS NOT NULL`\n- **Refunded:** `settled_at IS NOT NULL AND is_winner IS NULL`\n- **Wins:** `is_winner = TRUE`\n- **Losses:** `is_winner = FALSE`\n\nExample from `get-games-overview.ts` (line 161):\n```typescript\ncount(*) filter (where settled_at is not null and is_winner is null)::int as \"refund_entries\",\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. STANDARD QUERY FUNCTION SHAPE & NAMING CONVENTIONS\n\nBased on existing patterns (`get-games-overview.ts`, `get-peek-user-detail.ts`, `get-growth-referrals.ts`):\n\n#### **File naming:**\n- `get-games-overview.ts` — aggregated metrics + overview rows\n- `get-peek-user-detail.ts` — deep drill-down on one user\n- `get-growth-referrals.ts` — multi-function module (overview + list + graph)\n- **Recommendation for game rounds:** `get-game-rounds.ts` or `get-rounds-detail.ts` if grouping flipyou/potshot/closecall\n\n#### **Export structure:**\n```typescript\n// Constants\nexport const PEEK_GAME_ROUNDS_DEFAULT_LIMIT = 50;\nexport const PEEK_GAME_ROUNDS_MAX_LIMIT = 250;\n\n// Options type\nexport type GetGameRoundsOptions = {\n  sql?: Sql;\n  game: PeekGameId;\n  limit?: number;\n  filters?: Partial<GameRoundsFilters>;\n  sort?: PeekTableSort | null;\n  page?: number;\n};\n\n// Helper types for internal row mapping\ntype DBRoundRow = {\n  pda: string;\n  game: PeekGameId;\n  matchId: string;\n  phase: string;\n  creator: string | null;\n  /* ... game-specific fields ... */\n};\n\n// Exported row type extending PeekTableRowBase\nexport type PeekGameRoundRow = PeekTableRowBase & {\n  game: PeekGameId;\n  roundPda: string;\n  matchId: string;\n  phase: string;\n  creator: string | null;\n  /* ... */\n};\n\n// Main query function\nexport async function getGameRounds(\n  options: GetGameRoundsOptions = {},\n): Promise<PeekTableViewModel<PeekGameRoundRow>> {\n  const sql = options.sql ?? getSqlClient();\n  // ...\n  return {\n    columns: [/* ... */],\n    rows: [/* ... */],\n    pagination: { page, pageSize, totalCount, totalPages },\n    filters: [/* ... */],\n    sort: sort ?? null,\n    empty: { title: \"...\", body: null },\n  };\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 7. LAMPORT PRECISION & BIGINT HANDLING\n\nFrom `get-games-overview.ts`:\n\n```typescript\nfunction sumLamports(values: ReadonlyArray<string>): string {\n  // BigInt sum keeps u64 precision across per-game lamport totals; values\n  // are strings from the postgres driver.\n  let total = 0n;\n  for (const v of values) {\n    if (!v) continue;\n    try {\n      total += BigInt(v);\n    } catch {\n      // ignore unparsable values\n    }\n  }\n  return total.toString();\n}\n\nfunction readInt(value: number | string | null | undefined): number {\n  if (typeof value === \"number\" && Number.isFinite(value)) return value;\n  if (typeof value === \"string\") {\n    const parsed = Number.parseInt(value, 10);\n    return Number.isFinite(parsed) ? parsed : 0;\n  }\n  return 0;\n}\n\nfunction readSum(value: string | null | undefined): string {\n  return typeof value === \"string\" && value.length > 0 ? value : \"0\";\n}\n```\n\n**Rule:** All lamport sums and u64-sensitive counts arrive as `text` from postgres (due to `::text` cast or string BIGINT coercion); coerce via these helpers before display.\n\n---\n\n### 8. TEST SCAFFOLDING & MOCKING PATTERN\n\nFrom `get-games-overview.test.ts`:\n\n```typescript\ntype SqlCall = {\n  text: string;\n  values: ReadonlyArray<unknown>;\n};\n\ntype ResponseValue = ReadonlyArray<Record<string, unknown>> | Error;\n\ntype SqlMock = {\n  sql: Sql;\n  calls: ReadonlyArray<SqlCall>;\n};\n\nfunction createSqlMock(responses: ReadonlyArray<ResponseValue>): SqlMock {\n  const calls: SqlCall[] = [];\n  let cursor = 0;\n\n  const fn = (strings: TemplateStringsArray, ...values: unknown[]) => {\n    const text = [...strings].join(\"?\");\n    calls.push({ text, values: [...values] });\n    const next = responses[cursor++];\n    if (next instanceof Error) return Promise.reject(next);\n    return Promise.resolve(next ?? []);\n  };\n\n  const sql = fn as unknown as Sql;\n  return { sql, calls };\n}\n\n// Usage:\nconst mock = createSqlMock([\n  [/* first query response */],\n  [/* second query response */],\n]);\n\nconst result = await getGamesOverview({ sql: mock.sql, now });\n\nexpect(mock.calls).toHaveLength(2);\nexpect(mock.calls[0].text).toContain(\"from game_entries\");\n```\n\n**Key assertions:**\n- Count of parallel queries via `Promise.all()`\n- SQL text fragments (no exact match, use `.toContain()` for robustness)\n- Error handling: `expect(...).rejects.toThrow()`\n- String/number coercion tests (postgres returns text for `::int` casts)\n- Pagination + filtering behavior\n- Empty-state handling (zero-fill missing rows)\n\n---\n\n### 9. COMMAND-CENTER \"STUCK\" INTEGRATION\n\nThe peek types already define drill-down hrefs for stuck metrics:\n\n```typescript\n// From types:\nexport type PeekCommandCenterAttentionId =\n  | \"stuck_rounds_flipyou_potshot\"\n  | \"stuck_rounds_closecall\";\n\n// From get-command-center-attention.ts:\ndrilldownHref: \"/games?stuck=true\",           // flipyou/potshot stuck drill\ndrilldownHref: \"/games/closecall?stuck=true\", // closecall stuck drill\n```\n\n**If implementing per-game drill-down pages**, expect URL params like:\n- `?game=flipyou&stuck=true`\n- `?game=closecall&stuck=true`\n\n---\n\n### 10. PHASE ENUM & SETTLEMENT LIFECYCLE\n\n#### **FlipYou/PotShot (rounds table):**\n- `'created'` — round created, awaiting join\n- `'locked'` — join closed, awaiting commit reveal\n- `'settling'` — settlement in progress\n- `'settled'` — terminal, result finalized\n- `'expired'` — terminal, no settlement attempted\n\n#### **CloseCall (closecall_rounds table):**\n- `'open'` — round accepting bets\n- `'settled'` — terminal, Pyth resolved, payouts distributed\n- `'refunded'` — terminal, all bets refunded (e.g., circuit breaker)\n\n**Stuck detection:**\n- FlipYou/PotShot: NOT in {'settled', 'expired'}\n- CloseCall: = 'open'\n\n---\n\n### 11. KEY COLUMN NAMES & FIELD MAPPING\n\n#### **Rounds → Peek Row Mapping:**\n```\nDB Column           Peek Field (camelCase)\n---                 ---\npda                 roundPda / id (primary href)\ngame                game (PeekGameId)\nmatch_id            matchId\nphase               phase\ncreator             creator\ncreated_at::text    createdAt\nupdated_at::text    updatedAt\nsettled_at::text    settledAt\nsettle_attempts     settleAttempts\nsettle_tx           settleTx\nresult_side         resultSide\nwinner              winner\namount_lamports     amountLamports (if joining game_entries)\n```\n\n#### **CloseCall Rounds → Peek Row Mapping:**\n```\nDB Column           Peek Field\n---                 ---\npda                 roundPda / id\nround_id            matchId\nphase               phase\noutcome             outcome (pending|green|red|refund)\ncreated_at::text    createdAt\nsettled_at::text    settledAt\nopen_price          openPrice\nclose_price         closePrice\ngreen_pool          greenPool (lamports, text)\nred_pool            redPool (lamports, text)\ntotal_fee           totalFee (lamports, text)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 12. PAGINATION & LIMITS CONVENTIONS\n\nFrom `get-growth-referrals.ts`:\n\n```typescript\n// Per-feature constants:\nexport const PEEK_GROWTH_CLAIMS_DEFAULT_LIMIT = 100;\nexport const PEEK_GROWTH_CLAIMS_MAX_LIMIT = 500;\n\n// Helper:\nfunction clampLimit(\n  raw: number | undefined,\n  fallback: number,\n  max: number,\n): number {\n  if (typeof raw !== \"number\" || !Number.isFinite(raw)) return fallback;\n  const floored = Math.floor(raw);\n  if (floored <= 0) return 1;\n  return Math.min(max, floored);\n}\n\n// In function:\nconst limit = clampLimit(options.limit, DEFAULT_LIMIT, MAX_LIMIT);\n```\n\n**Pagination formula:**\n```typescript\nconst totalPages = Math.max(1, Math.ceil(totalCount / pageSize));\nconst offset = (page - 1) * pageSize;\n// In SQL: LIMIT pageSize OFFSET offset\n```\n\n---\n\n### 13. FILTER TYPE PATTERNS\n\nFrom `peek.ts`:\n\n```typescript\nexport type PeekTableFilter = {\n  id: string;                    // URL-addressable filter key\n  label: string;                 // Human-readable name\n  kind: PeekFilterKind;          // \"text\" | \"select\" | \"boolean\" | \"date\" | \"dateRange\"\n  value: string | null;          // Current filter value (URL param)\n  options: ReadonlyArray<PeekFilterOption> | null;  // For \"select\" kind\n  placeholder: string | null;\n  required: boolean;\n};\n\nexport type PeekFilterOption = {\n  value: string;\n  label: string;\n};\n\n// Example filters for game rounds:\nconst filters: PeekTableFilter[] = [\n  {\n    id: \"game\",\n    label: \"Game\",\n    kind: \"select\",\n    value: options.filters?.game ?? null,\n    options: PEEK_GAME_IDS.map(g => ({ value: g, label: g })),\n    placeholder: null,\n    required: false,\n  },\n  {\n    id: \"phase\",\n    label: \"Phase\",\n    kind: \"select\",\n    value: options.filters?.phase ?? null,\n    options: [\"created\", \"locked\", \"settling\", \"settled\", \"expired\"].map(p => \n      ({ value: p, label: p })\n    ),\n    placeholder: null,\n    required: false,\n  },\n  {\n    id: \"stuck\",\n    label: \"Stuck status\",\n    kind: \"boolean\",\n    value: options.filters?.stuck ?? null,\n    options: null,\n    placeholder: null,\n    required: false,\n  },\n];\n```\n\n---\n\n### SUMMARY: Quick Reference for `get-game-rounds.ts`\n\n1. **Client:** `const sql = options.sql ?? getSqlClient() as unknown as Sql`\n2. **Refunds:** `is_winner IS NULL AND settled_at IS NOT NULL`\n3. **Stuck (flipyou/potshot):** `phase IN ('created','locked','settling') AND (created_at < now()-interval OR settle_attempts > threshold)`\n4. **Stuck (closecall):** `phase = 'open' AND created_at < now()-interval`\n5. **BigInt sums:** Use `sumLamports()` helper + `readInt()` / `readSum()` for type coercion\n6. **Pagination:** `OFFSET (page-1)*pageSize LIMIT pageSize`, compute totalPages\n7. **Return type:** `PeekTableViewModel<YourRowType extends PeekTableRowBase>`\n8. **Tests:** Mock SQL with `createSqlMock([responses])`, assert on query counts + text fragments\n9. **Game ID:** Type as `PeekGameId` (literal union of three), filter via `PEEK_GAME_IDS` array check\n10. **Metrics:** Full FR-4 bookkeeping if returning summary strip alongside detail rows\n\nAll files are read-only; no ALTERs in migrations. Phase/game enums enforced by CHECK constraints at the DB level."}],"totalDurationMs":77362,"totalTokens":83361,"totalToolUseCount":20,"usage":{"input_tokens":4,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2151,"cache_read_input_tokens":75388,"output_tokens":5818,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2151},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":4,"output_tokens":5818,"cache_read_input_tokens":75388,"cache_creation_inpu